== Purpose ==
Template for creating symbols for physics particles.

== Arguments ==

:'''1''' The main symbol character(s) for the particle

Named arguments:
:'''anti''' = yes &ndash; this puts a bar over the symbol
:'''TL'''  = What goes into the top left corner (optional)
:'''BL'''  = What goes into the bottom left corner (optional)
:'''TR'''  = What goes into the top right corner (optional)
:'''BR'''  = What goes into the bottom right corner (optional)
:'''link''' = Page to which the symbol should link
Deprecated:
:''BLc'' = ''Originally used to supply the count of characters in BL argument.''
:''BRc'' = ''Originally used to supply the count of characters in BR argument.''

Here's a diagram:

:{{huge|{{Physics particle|anti=yes|X|TR=TR|BR=BR|BRc=2.5|TL=TL|BL=BL|BLc=2}}}}

== Examples ==
[[Template:Subatomic particle]] uses this template to display particles, e.g.:

<code><nowiki>{{Subatomic particle|link=yes|Electron}}</nowiki></code> → {{Subatomic particle|link=yes|Electron}} is the same as
:<code><nowiki>{{Physics particle|e|TR=&minus;|link=Electron}}</nowiki></code> &rarr; {{Physics particle|e|TR=&minus;|link=Electron}} (an [[electron]])
<code><nowiki>{{Subatomic particle|Strange antib0}}</nowiki></code> → {{Subatomic particle|Strange antib0}} is the same as
:<code><nowiki>{{Physics particle|anti=yes|B|TR=0|BR=s|BRc=1}}</nowiki></code> &rarr; {{Physics particle|anti=yes|B|TR=0|BR=s|BRc=1}} (a [[List of mesons|meson]])

The templates in [[:Category:核素模板]] use this template to display nuclides, e.g.:

<code><nowiki>{{ComplexNuclide|deuterium|link=yes}}</nowiki></code> → {{ComplexNuclide|deuterium|link=yes}} is the same as
:<code><nowiki>{{Physics particle|D|TL=2|BL=1|BR=1|link=deuterium}}</nowiki></code> &rarr; {{Physics particle|D|TL=2|BL=1|BR=1|link=deuterium}}
<code><nowiki>{{Element2|link=yes|hydrogen|charge=+}}</nowiki></code> → {{Element2|link=yes|hydrogen|charge=+}} is the same as
:<code><nowiki>{{Physics particle|H|TR=+|link=hydrogen}}</nowiki></code> &rarr; {{Physics particle|H|TR=+|link=hydrogen}}

